data.current_description: Gets the metadata of the specified PhotoSequence via the Operation interface. This method returns the following three types of responses: * `Operation.done` = false, if the processing of PhotoSequence is not finished yet. * `Operation.done` = true and `Operation.error` is populated, if there was an error in processing. * `Operation.done` = true and `Operation.response` is poulated, which contains a PhotoSequence message. This method returns the following error codes: * google.rpc.Code.PERMISSION_DENIED if the requesting user did not create the requested PhotoSequence. * google.rpc.Code.NOT_FOUND if the requested PhotoSequence does not exist.
data.summary_suggestion: Retrieve PhotoSequence metadata and processing status
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves the metadata and processing status of a specified PhotoSequence using the long-running Operation interface. Returns one of three states: (1) Operation.done=false if processing is ongoing, (2) Operation.done=true with Operation.error if processing failed, or (3) Operation.done=true with Operation.response containing the PhotoSequence object if successful. Requires the sequenceId parameter. Returns PERMISSION_DENIED if the user did not create the PhotoSequence, or NOT_FOUND if the PhotoSequence does not exist.

data.current_description: After the client finishes uploading the photo with the returned UploadRef, CreatePhoto publishes the uploaded Photo to Street View on Google Maps. Currently, the only way to set heading, pitch, and roll in CreatePhoto is through the [Photo Sphere XMP metadata](https://developers.google.com/streetview/spherical-metadata) in the photo bytes. CreatePhoto ignores the `pose.heading`, `pose.pitch`, `pose.roll`, `pose.altitude`, and `pose.level` fields in Pose. This method returns the following error codes: * google.rpc.Code.INVALID_ARGUMENT if the request is malformed or if the uploaded photo is not a 360 photo. * google.rpc.Code.NOT_FOUND if the upload reference does not exist. * google.rpc.Code.RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED if the account has reached the storage limit.
data.summary_suggestion: Publish uploaded 360 photo to Street View
data.description_suggestion: Publishes an uploaded 360 photo to Google Street View. Requires a valid UploadRef from a prior startUpload call. The photo must contain Photo Sphere XMP metadata for orientation data; pose.heading, pose.pitch, pose.roll, pose.altitude, and pose.level fields are ignored. Returns the created Photo object with metadata. Errors: INVALID_ARGUMENT if photo is not 360 or request is malformed, NOT_FOUND if UploadRef is invalid, RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED if storage limit reached.
data.reasoning: Missing summary entirely. Description is comprehensive but lacks clarity on inputs (UploadRef requirement) and outputs (Photo object returned). Added explicit input/output details and reorganized error codes for better AI agent understanding of when to use this operation.

data.current_description: Creates an upload session to start uploading photo bytes. The method uses the upload URL of the returned UploadRef to upload the bytes for the Photo. In addition to the photo requirements shown in https://support.google.com/maps/answer/7012050?ref_topic=6275604, the photo must meet the following requirements: * Photo Sphere XMP metadata must be included in the photo metadata. See https://developers.google.com/streetview/spherical-metadata for the required fields. * The pixel size of the photo must meet the size requirements listed in https://support.google.com/maps/answer/7012050?ref_topic=6275604, and the photo must be a full 360 horizontally. After the upload completes, the method uses UploadRef with CreatePhoto to create the Photo object entry.
data.description_suggestion: Initiates an upload session for a 360 photo. Returns an UploadRef containing the upload URL for transferring photo bytes. Photo must be full 360 degrees horizontally and include Photo Sphere XMP metadata with required orientation fields. Pixel dimensions must meet Street View requirements. Use the returned UploadRef with CreatePhoto to publish the photo after upload completes. Errors: INVALID_ARGUMENT if request is malformed, NOT_FOUND if upload reference is invalid.
